Listeriosis has already been responsible for 183 deaths, and it’s likely that the actual death toll is higher. That means you don’t really want to be taking any chances, so best you get up to speed with exactly which products aren’t safe for wolfing down. Even the Southern Suburbs’ Holy Grail, Woolies, has been affected – a fact that has shaken many to their core – and some of the country’s biggest retailers have issued lengthy recalls. Business Insider SA compiled this list, starting with Pick n Pay: Pick n Pay Rainbow Enterprise 
